Follow the bag shape as shown in the diagram:Leave the base of the tube intact. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut the bag lid or top as shown by the lines within the pink area of the diagram. Cut a slight curve across the top of the base part of the bag, as shown in the diagram. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/84/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/84/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut off a ring from the very top part of the tube (the area just under the neck that you've already removed). This will become the bag's handle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d0/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d0/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use a hole punch to punch out a circle in the top part of the bag, as shown in the diagram above. The hole must be the same size as the plastic bead you're using as the button clasp. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

For the smaller hole, use a small sharp object to pierce it. You may want to leave making this until the next section (Making the Button Clasp). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b3/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b3/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If needed, tidy up the base of the bag by trimming (but don't cut it open). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet6.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet6.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-2Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If the tube already has a design printed on it that you're happy with, you can skip this step. On the other hand, if you don't like the proprietary design, you can fix it using decorative tape.Stick on a basic shape or make a collage using decorative tape. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0e/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0e/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make sure that it covers up any ugly print or imagery that you don't want to show. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/30/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/30/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use any other decorative items to embellish as liked. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/59/Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Small-Bag-from-a-Tube-Container-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
